FBIS4-21913 "jptot015__l94078" JPRS-TOT-94-015-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 6 April 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL Hamas Carbomb in 'Afula Kills Eight, Wounds 50 Hamas Carbomb in 'Afula Kills Eight, Wounds 50 Suicide Bomber LD0604111194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1030 GMT 6 Apr 94 LD0604111194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el English BFN [Excerpts] First to 'Afula where a car bomb exploded three meters from a bus. Latest reports say five people were killed, another 35 at least wounded. The incident occurred near a cultural center. Apparently there was a suicide bomber in the car. Neil Samba has the story. Neil. [Samba] The explosion occurred at around 1230 near the cultural center of 'Afula not far from the town's ... er, in the center of the 'Afula, not far from the town's main auditorium. Latest reports speak of five dead and 35 injured, but these figures are changing and constantly being updated. Reports from [words indistinct] say that the injuries range from light to serious. Some of the injured were on the bus and others were waiting at a nearby bus station. All of the injured are being taken to the (?Haemic) hospital. The evacuation continues at this hour. We've just heard though that two of those seriously injured were taken to Haifa, Haifa's (?Rambam) hospital. Northern district police commander Jacob Grenel was the first to confirm that it was in fact a car bomb that exploded near an Egged bus, but he said it's not clear whether it was a suicide bomber or whether the bomb was set off by remote control. The explosion took place three to four meters from a bus stop. [passage omitted].
